# [[.AppName]]

A Go web application built with hexagonal architecture and generated by [scaffold](https://github.com/esrid/scaffold).

[[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]**Stack:** [[if .IsHTML]]html/template (pure SSR, HTMX vendored but opt-in)[[else]]templ (compiled components, HTMX-wired)[[end]] · plain CSS (web/static/app.css) · [[if eq .DB "postgres"]]PostgreSQL[[else]]SQLite[[end]] · stdlib net/http[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "rest"]]**Stack:** JSON REST API · stdlib net/http · [[if eq .DB "postgres"]]PostgreSQL[[else]]SQLite[[end]] · TypeScript/esbuild[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "grpc"]]**Stack:** REST JSON + gRPC · stdlib net/http · [[if eq .DB "postgres"]]PostgreSQL[[else]]SQLite[[end]] · protobuf[[end]]

Requires **Go 1.27** — `id` fields are UUIDv7 strings generated with the stdlib `uuid` package (`uuid.NewV7()`, stdlib since Go 1.27).

## Getting started

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — set DATABASE_URL and SECRET_KEY at minimum
make run
```

[[if eq .APIMode "rest"]]Server runs on `:8080`. Add models with `scaffold gen`:

```bash
scaffold gen Product name:string! price:float! description:string
# → GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/products
```

List endpoints return newest-first and accept `?limit=` (default 20, max 100)
and `?offset=` query parameters.
[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]Server runs on `:8080`. Add models with `scaffold gen`:

```bash
scaffold gen Product name:string! price:float! description:string
# → /products  (list, show, create, edit pages)
```
[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "grpc"]]HTTP server on `:8080`, gRPC on `:50051`. Add models with `scaffold gen`:

```bash
scaffold gen Order status:string! total:float!
make proto   # compile .proto → Go pb package
# → /api/orders (REST) + gRPC ProductService
```
[[end]]

## Project structure

```
internal/
├── core/
│   ├── domain/       # structs, Validate(), error types
│   ├── ports/        # repository and service interfaces
│   └── services/     # business logic
└── adapters/
    ├── http/         # [[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]SSR handlers, bindForm[[else]]JSON CRUD handler[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "grpc"]]
    ├── store/        # SQL queries
    └── grpc/         # gRPC handlers, translateError[[else]]
    └── store/        # SQL queries[[end]]
internal/app/
├── config.go         # env-based config
├── custom.go         # wire your own services here (yours)[[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]
└── app.go            # server startup, dependency wiring, route mounting —
                       # ALL IN ONE FILE, `scaffold gen`/`destroy` only rewrite
                       # the content inside `// scaffold:*:start/end` marker
                       # comments; everything else is yours[[else]]
├── app.go            # server startup, route mounting (yours)
├── routes_gen.go     # model route registration (auto-regenerated in full)
└── registry.go       # dependency wiring (auto-regenerated in full)[[end]]
[[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]web/
├── static/app.css    # plain CSS, edit freely — served at /static/app.css
[[if .IsTempl]]└── views/
    ├── layout.templ  # shared page layout component
    ├── home.templ
    ├── helpers.go    # display/truthy template helpers
    └── {model}.templ # List/Form/Show components (write-once — yours)

Install the templ CLI once (`go install github.com/a-h/templ/cmd/templ@latest`),
then run `make generate` after changing any .templ file. `make build`/`make run`
run it for you.
[[else]]└── templates/
    ├── layout/base.html  # shared page layout
    ├── home.html
    └── {model}.html      # List/Form/Show templates (write-once — yours)

No compile step — html/template renders directly from web/templates.
`htmx.min.js` is vendored (web/static/js/) and already loaded in the layout,
but generated views use plain `<form>` submits (pure SSR) — add `hx-*`
attributes to the write-once `.html` views yourself where you want partial-page
updates.
[[end]][[end]][[if eq .APIMode "rest"]]web/
├── src/              # TypeScript + CSS source
└── dist/             # built assets (committed for zero-build deploys)
[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "grpc"]]internal/adapters/grpc/pb/
├── {model}.proto     # auto-generated, compile with: make proto
└── {model}.pb.go     # generated by buf, lives beside the .proto
[[end]]```

## scaffold commands

```bash
# Add a new model
scaffold gen Article title:string! body:string! views:int

# Add a field to an existing model (generates ALTER TABLE migration)
scaffold gen Article title:string! body:string! views:int published:bool!

# Remove a model
scaffold destroy Article

# Add a model without generating HTTP/gRPC handlers
scaffold gen Article title:string! body:string! --no-handler

# Preview without writing
scaffold gen Article title:string! --dry-run
```

## Field types

| Type | Go | SQL |
|------|----|-----|
| `string!` | `string` | `TEXT NOT NULL` |
| `string` | `*string` | `TEXT` |
| `int!` | `int` | `INTEGER NOT NULL` |
| `float!` | `float64` | `REAL NOT NULL` |
| `bool!` | `bool` | `INTEGER NOT NULL` |
| `time!` | `time.Time` | `DATETIME NOT NULL` |
| `json!` | `json.RawMessage` | `TEXT NOT NULL` |
| `[]<type>` (or `<type>,array`) | Go slice (e.g. `[]string`) | JSON-encoded `TEXT` / native array |

**Array fields** can be declared using either the shell-safe `<type>,array` suffix (e.g. `tags:string,array!`, `scores:int,array`) or the legacy `[]<type>` prefix (e.g. `tags:[]string!`, `scores:[]int`).
Valid element types: `string`, `text`, `int`, `int64`, `float`, `float64`, `bool`.

Useful modifiers: `,unique`, `,index`, `,default=value`, `,fk=table`, `,cascade` (requires `fk=`), `,setnull` (requires `fk=`), `,check=expr` (comma syntax is shell-safe in zsh/bash). Per-op middleware: `scaffold gen Model --middleware update:RequireAuth`.

Field names that are SQL reserved words (`order`, `user`, `group`, …) or that
collide with the auto-managed `id`/`created_at`/`updated_at` columns are
rejected at generation time.

> [!NOTE]
> **Migrations:** adding a NOT NULL field to an existing model emits an
> `ALTER TABLE` with a zero-value `DEFAULT` so the migration applies cleanly to
> existing rows. Changing the **type or modifiers** of an existing field updates
> the code and `schema.sql` but writes **no migration** — scaffold prints a
> warning and you write the column alteration by hand.

> [!NOTE]
> **Struct Field Packing:** To optimize memory alignment and minimize padding, `scaffold` automatically sorts all generated struct fields descending by their byte size in `domain/{model}_gen.go`.

## What scaffold manages vs. what's yours

| File | Ownership |
|------|-----------|
| `domain/{model}_gen.go` — struct, GetID/WithID | scaffold regenerates |
| `domain/{model}.go` — `Validate()` + methods | **yours** |
| `ports/{model}.go` | written once, never touched |
| `services/{model}_service_gen.go` | scaffold regenerates |
| `services/{model}_service.go` | **yours** |
| `store/{model}_store_gen.go` | scaffold regenerates |
| `store/{model}_store.go` | **yours** — add custom queries here |[[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]
| `app/app.go` — content inside `// scaffold:*` markers | scaffold regenerates, scoped per model |
| `app/app.go` — everything else | **yours**, never touched |[[else]]
| `app/registry.go`, `app/routes_gen.go` | scaffold regenerates, in full |
| `app/app.go` | **yours** |[[end]]
| `app/custom.go` | **yours** |[[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]
| `http/{model}_handler_gen.go` | scaffold regenerates |
| `http/{model}_handler.go` | **yours** — `registerCustomRoutes` lives here |
| `web/[[if .IsTempl]]views/{model}.templ[[else]]templates/{model}.html[[end]]` | written once — **yours** (refresh with `scaffold gen {Model} --regen-views`) |[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "grpc"]]
| `adapters/grpc/{model}_handler_gen.go` | scaffold regenerates |
| `adapters/grpc/shared.go` | written once |
| `internal/adapters/grpc/pb/{model}.proto` | scaffold regenerates |[[end]]

## Adding custom logic

**Validation** — in `internal/core/domain/{model}.go`:

```go
func (p Product) Validate() error {
    if p.Price <= 0 {
        return &domain.ValidationError{
            Entity: "Product",
            Errors: map[string]string{"price": "must be greater than zero"},
        }
    }
    return nil
}
```

**Custom queries** — in `internal/adapters/store/{model}_store.go`:

```go
func (s *ProductStore) FindBySlug(ctx context.Context, slug string) (*domain.Product, error) {
	[[if eq .DB "sqlite"]]// SQLite: plain positional Scan, same pattern as the generated Get/List.
	row := s.db.QueryRowContext(ctx, "SELECT id, name, price, active, created_at, updated_at FROM products WHERE slug = ?", slug)
	var p domain.Product
	if err := row.Scan(&p.ID, &p.Name, &p.Price, &p.Active, &p.CreatedAt, &p.UpdatedAt); err != nil {
		return nil, err
	}
	return &p, nil[[else]]// Postgres: pgx's struct-mapping helpers.
	rows, err := s.pool.Query(ctx, "SELECT id, name, price, active, created_at, updated_at FROM products WHERE slug = $1", slug)
	if err != nil {
		return nil, err
	}
	return pgx.CollectOneRow(rows, pgx.RowToAddrOfStructByName[domain.Product])[[end]]
}
```

**Business logic** — in `internal/core/services/{model}_service.go`:

```go
func (s *ProductService) Publish(ctx context.Context, id string) error {
    // your logic here
}
```
[[if eq .APIMode "ssr"]]
**Extra routes** — in `internal/adapters/http/{model}_handler.go`:

```go
// registerCustomRoutes is always called by the generated Router() — routes
// added here survive regeneration.
func (h *ProductHandler) registerCustomRoutes(mux *http.ServeMux) {
    mux.HandleFunc("GET /featured", h.Featured)
}

func (h *ProductHandler) Featured(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    // render a custom template
}
```
[[end]][[if eq .APIMode "grpc"]]
**After scaffold gen**, compile protos:

```bash
make proto
# Compiles internal/adapters/grpc/pb/*.proto into *.pb.go beside them
```
[[end]]

## Connecting external services

New service = one interface (port) + one implementation (adapter) + wire in registry.

```
ports/storage.go      ← interface  (FileStorage, Mailer, Cache…)
adapters/s3/          ← implementation
app/custom.go         ← inject (has access to cfg + registry)
```

The core never imports SDK packages. Adapters are the only place that knows about AWS, Redis, Stripe, etc.

## Environment variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | [[if eq .DB "sqlite"]]`file:app.db?_journal_mode=WAL&_foreign_keys=on`[[else]]`postgres://localhost/[[.AppName]]?sslmode=disable`[[end]] | Database connection |
| `SECRET_KEY` | — | Required — `openssl rand -hex 32` |
| `ADDR` | `:8080` | HTTP listen address |[[if eq .APIMode "grpc"]]
| `GRPC_ADDR` | `:50051` | gRPC listen address |[[end]]
| `APP_ENV` | `development` | `production` enables JSON logs + embedded assets |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `info` | `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error` |
| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` | `*` | Allowed CORS origins (comma-separated list, or `*` for all) |

## Production checklist

```
□ SECRET_KEY strong (openssl rand -hex 32)
□ APP_ENV=production
□ LOG_LEVEL=warn
□ HTTPS via reverse proxy (Caddy recommended)
□ Uptime monitor on /health
□ Error tracking (Sentry / GlitchTip)
[[if eq .DB "sqlite"]]□ SQLite backup via Litestream → S3
[[end]]□ CORS restricted to your domain in middleware.go
```
